{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/slammer/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"A*Morale","author":"Alessio Morale","siteUrl":"https://blog.alessiomorale.com"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"5949abb4-a6d3-5bf6-a892-20f5dcd0861c","excerpt":"This project started a few years ago as my learning platform for robotic in general and ROS. At that time i was working mostly with drones, but I realised thatâ€¦","html":"<p>This project started a few years ago as my learning platform for robotic in general and ROS.</p>\n<p>At that time i was working mostly with drones, but I realised that testing things like mapping and navigation would have been much more harder and almost impossible indoor. For this reason, I started learning the basics of rovers and mobile robotics. Thus Slammer was born.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#slammer-tech-specs\">Slammer tech specs</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#mechanical-and-electrical-specs\">Mechanical and electrical specs</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#electronics-and-sensors\">Electronics and sensors</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#software\">Software</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><a href=\"#ros\">ROS</a></li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#teleop\">Teleop</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#updated-expresslrs-lora-24ghz-teleop\">Updated ExpressLRS Lora 2.4GHz Teleop</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#old-ds4drv-bluetooth-joypad\">Old DS4DRV bluetooth joypad</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><a href=\"#video\">Video</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#additional-pictures\">Additional pictures</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/3ab7f86d0bb51cdb8b942c748cf4c8d6/5829c/IMG_20211008_183528.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin: 7vw 0; max-width: 1360px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/3ab7f86d0bb51cdb8b942c748cf4c8d6/51a8e/IMG_20211008_183528.webp 340w,\n/static/3ab7f86d0bb51cdb8b942c748cf4c8d6/713b7/IMG_20211008_183528.webp 680w,\n/static/3ab7f86d0bb51cdb8b942c748cf4c8d6/54376/IMG_20211008_183528.webp 1360w,\n/static/3ab7f86d0bb51cdb8b942c748cf4c8d6/0be89/IMG_20211008_183528.webp 2040w,\n/static/3ab7f86d0bb51cdb8b942c748cf4c8d6/71194/IMG_20211008_183528.webp 2720w,\n/static/3ab7f86d0bb51cdb8b942c748cf4c8d6/2138d/IMG_20211008_183528.webp 3109w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 1360px) 100vw, 1360px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/3ab7f86d0bb51cdb8b942c748cf4c8d6/2e524/IMG_20211008_183528.jpg 340w,\n/static/3ab7f86d0bb51cdb8b942c748cf4c8d6/d330d/IMG_20211008_183528.jpg 680w,\n/static/3ab7f86d0bb51cdb8b942c748cf4c8d6/6c26c/IMG_20211008_183528.jpg 1360w,\n/static/3ab7f86d0bb51cdb8b942c748cf4c8d6/afd2d/IMG_20211008_183528.jpg 2040w,\n/static/3ab7f86d0bb51cdb8b942c748cf4c8d6/f4749/IMG_20211008_183528.jpg 2720w,\n/static/3ab7f86d0bb51cdb8b942c748cf4c8d6/5829c/IMG_20211008_183528.jpg 3109w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 1360px) 100vw, 1360px\"\n          type=\"image/jpeg\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n          src=\"/static/3ab7f86d0bb51cdb8b942c748cf4c8d6/6c26c/IMG_20211008_183528.jpg\"\n          alt=\"Slammer\"\n          title=\"\"\n          src=\"/static/3ab7f86d0bb51cdb8b942c748cf4c8d6/6c26c/IMG_20211008_183528.jpg\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n      </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>In its initial configuration it used four gearmotors for its locomotion using the <a href=\"./unav2\">uNav2 prototype</a>. It was handling the feedback (encoders) on two motors only, with the two others (identical) simply wired in parallel. Not exactly optimal.</p>\n<p>Recently I update the mechanical part using two planetary gear motors and a system of pulleys and belts to link front and rear wheels on each side.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/f45b226167953a8ce1289fd2ca7669ee/d1cca/IMG_20210425_164140.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin: 7vw 0; max-width: 1360px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 133.23529411764707%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/f45b226167953a8ce1289fd2ca7669ee/51a8e/IMG_20210425_164140.webp 340w,\n/static/f45b226167953a8ce1289fd2ca7669ee/713b7/IMG_20210425_164140.webp 680w,\n/static/f45b226167953a8ce1289fd2ca7669ee/54376/IMG_20210425_164140.webp 1360w,\n/static/f45b226167953a8ce1289fd2ca7669ee/0be89/IMG_20210425_164140.webp 2040w,\n/static/f45b226167953a8ce1289fd2ca7669ee/71194/IMG_20210425_164140.webp 2720w,\n/static/f45b226167953a8ce1289fd2ca7669ee/817da/IMG_20210425_164140.webp 2736w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 1360px) 100vw, 1360px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/f45b226167953a8ce1289fd2ca7669ee/2e524/IMG_20210425_164140.jpg 340w,\n/static/f45b226167953a8ce1289fd2ca7669ee/d330d/IMG_20210425_164140.jpg 680w,\n/static/f45b226167953a8ce1289fd2ca7669ee/6c26c/IMG_20210425_164140.jpg 1360w,\n/static/f45b226167953a8ce1289fd2ca7669ee/afd2d/IMG_20210425_164140.jpg 2040w,\n/static/f45b226167953a8ce1289fd2ca7669ee/f4749/IMG_20210425_164140.jpg 2720w,\n/static/f45b226167953a8ce1289fd2ca7669ee/d1cca/IMG_20210425_164140.jpg 2736w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 1360px) 100vw, 1360px\"\n          type=\"image/jpeg\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n          src=\"/static/f45b226167953a8ce1289fd2ca7669ee/6c26c/IMG_20210425_164140.jpg\"\n          alt=\"Slammer @ Maker Faire EU 2021\"\n          title=\"\"\n          src=\"/static/f45b226167953a8ce1289fd2ca7669ee/6c26c/IMG_20210425_164140.jpg\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n      </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p><div class=\"gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper\" style=\"padding-bottom: 50%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden; margin-bottom: 1.0725rem\" > <div class=\"embedVideo-container\"> <iframe title src=\"https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/TDbqgjx-6oY?rel=0\" class=\"embedVideo-iframe\" style=\"border:0; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; \" loading=\"lazy\" allowfullscreen sandbox=\"allow-same-origin allow-scripts allow-popups\"></iframe> </div> </div></p>\n<p>The control board is still my trusted <a href=\"./unav2\">UNAV2 prototype</a> (links to the <a href=\"https://github.com/AlessioMorale/unav2_hardware/tree/master/integrated_board\">hardware</a>, <a href=\"https://github.com/AlessioMorale/unav2_stm32\">firmware</a> and <a href=\"https://github.com/AlessioMorale/unav2_ros\">ROS drivers</a>).</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/4ded19c71f4de9b568de658c580a9a70/cbe2c/DSC8028.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin: 7vw 0; max-width: 1360px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/4ded19c71f4de9b568de658c580a9a70/51a8e/DSC8028.webp 340w,\n/static/4ded19c71f4de9b568de658c580a9a70/713b7/DSC8028.webp 680w,\n/static/4ded19c71f4de9b568de658c580a9a70/54376/DSC8028.webp 1360w,\n/static/4ded19c71f4de9b568de658c580a9a70/521a5/DSC8028.webp 2000w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 1360px) 100vw, 1360px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/4ded19c71f4de9b568de658c580a9a70/2e524/DSC8028.jpg 340w,\n/static/4ded19c71f4de9b568de658c580a9a70/d330d/DSC8028.jpg 680w,\n/static/4ded19c71f4de9b568de658c580a9a70/6c26c/DSC8028.jpg 1360w,\n/static/4ded19c71f4de9b568de658c580a9a70/cbe2c/DSC8028.jpg 2000w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 1360px) 100vw, 1360px\"\n          type=\"image/jpeg\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n          src=\"/static/4ded19c71f4de9b568de658c580a9a70/6c26c/DSC8028.jpg\"\n          alt=\"uNav2\"\n          title=\"\"\n          src=\"/static/4ded19c71f4de9b568de658c580a9a70/6c26c/DSC8028.jpg\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n      </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2>Slammer tech specs</h2>\n<h3>Mechanical and electrical specs</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Size(LxWxH): 32 x 20 x 15 cm</li>\n<li>Ground clearance: 4cm</li>\n<li>Weight: 2 Kg</li>\n<li>Motors: 2x 28mm planetary gearmotors - 10W - 3Nm (stall torque)</li>\n<li>Battery: 4S Li-ion battery pack with integrated balancer/protection, 3000mAh (replacement part for vacuum robots)</li>\n<li>Chassis: 3D printed, assembled using two 300mm 20x20 modular profiles as main carrier frame (parts design to be uploaded soon)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Electronics and sensors</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.nvidia.com/object/embedded-systems-dev-kits-modules.html\">NVIDIA Jetson Nano</a>.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://blog.alessiomorale.com/unav2\">Unav2</a> motor controller.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.intelrealsense.com/depth-camera-d435/\">Intel Realsense D435</a> depth camera</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.slamtec.com/en/Lidar/A1\">Slamtech A1 LIDAR</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.bosch-sensortec.com/products/smart-sensors/bno055/\">Bosch Sensortec BNO055 based imu</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ExpressLRS/ExpressLRS\">Express LRS based teleop over Lora</a> using custom CRSF driver <a href=\"https://github.com/AlessioMorale/ros_crsf_driver\">ros-crsf-driver</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://littlewire.github.io/\">Littlewire</a> based WS281x smart lights based notification system, using custom <a href=\"https://github.com/AlessioMorale/ros_signalling\">ROS signalling driver</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Software</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>main <a href=\"https://github.com/AlessioMorale/slammer_rover\">ROS robot packages</a></li>\n<li>ROS Melodic running on Jetpack 32.5 based <a href=\"https://github.com/AlessioMorale/jetson-ros-perception\">Docker images</a></li>\n<li>OpenCV, PCL &#x26; librealsense compiled to use CUDA acceleration and offload the CPU.</li>\n<li>Custom <a href=\"https://github.com/AlessioMorale/jetson-ros-rtabmap\">Docker</a> image running RTABMap &#x26; ROS wrappers recompiled to use the above libraries</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/AlessioMorale/slammer_rover\">complete system</a> can be started using <a href=\"https://github.com/AlessioMorale/slammer_rover/tree/master/docker\">docker-compose</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/fcb74c3850e703ed754f05e7bb58ae04/f8e5b/IMG_20210321_235444.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin: 7vw 0; max-width: 1360px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 69.11764705882352%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/fcb74c3850e703ed754f05e7bb58ae04/51a8e/IMG_20210321_235444.webp 340w,\n/static/fcb74c3850e703ed754f05e7bb58ae04/713b7/IMG_20210321_235444.webp 680w,\n/static/fcb74c3850e703ed754f05e7bb58ae04/54376/IMG_20210321_235444.webp 1360w,\n/static/fcb74c3850e703ed754f05e7bb58ae04/0be89/IMG_20210321_235444.webp 2040w,\n/static/fcb74c3850e703ed754f05e7bb58ae04/71194/IMG_20210321_235444.webp 2720w,\n/static/fcb74c3850e703ed754f05e7bb58ae04/b4fca/IMG_20210321_235444.webp 3112w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 1360px) 100vw, 1360px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/fcb74c3850e703ed754f05e7bb58ae04/2e524/IMG_20210321_235444.jpg 340w,\n/static/fcb74c3850e703ed754f05e7bb58ae04/d330d/IMG_20210321_235444.jpg 680w,\n/static/fcb74c3850e703ed754f05e7bb58ae04/6c26c/IMG_20210321_235444.jpg 1360w,\n/static/fcb74c3850e703ed754f05e7bb58ae04/afd2d/IMG_20210321_235444.jpg 2040w,\n/static/fcb74c3850e703ed754f05e7bb58ae04/f4749/IMG_20210321_235444.jpg 2720w,\n/static/fcb74c3850e703ed754f05e7bb58ae04/f8e5b/IMG_20210321_235444.jpg 3112w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 1360px) 100vw, 1360px\"\n          type=\"image/jpeg\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n          src=\"/static/fcb74c3850e703ed754f05e7bb58ae04/6c26c/IMG_20210321_235444.jpg\"\n          alt=\"Jetson Nano\"\n          title=\"\"\n          src=\"/static/fcb74c3850e703ed754f05e7bb58ae04/6c26c/IMG_20210321_235444.jpg\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n      </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2>ROS</h2>\n<p>The system is currently based on ROS Melodic.</p>\n<p>One of my requisites is to be able to use as much as possible the available GPU to free the CPU for tasks that cannot take advantage of it. For this reason I recompiled from sources both the Realsense drivers, OpenCV and part of RTABMap prerequisites (PCL).</p>\n<p>As rebuilding the software onboard is a very slow process I managed to set up a series of Docker containers and their related CI process so that they are automatically built using Github actions (for example <a href=\"https://github.com/AlessioMorale/jetson-ros-rtabmap\">ROS + RTABMap</a> repository).</p>\n<p>The ROS workspace used to run Slammer is available in my Github, <a href=\"https://github.com/AlessioMorale/rover_launch_files\">here</a>. The docker folder contains several docker compose files used to start the various software components one by one, everything completely dockerised.</p>\n<h2>Teleop</h2>\n<h3>Updated ExpressLRS Lora 2.4GHz Teleop</h3>\n<p>As part of the changes to use the robot at the last Maker Faire in Rome (8-10 Oct 2021), I replaced the bluetooth joypad with an <a href=\"https://www.expresslrs.org\">ExpressLRS</a> receiver and a Jumper T-Lite transmitter. The additional benefit is the possibility to rely on the extensive <a href=\"https://www.open-tx.org/\">OpenTX</a> telemetry and configurability.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/ad8f512f9f55c159c75ce39cb6ecb90d/9041d/IMG_20211006_232200.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin: 7vw 0; max-width: 1360px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/ad8f512f9f55c159c75ce39cb6ecb90d/51a8e/IMG_20211006_232200.webp 340w,\n/static/ad8f512f9f55c159c75ce39cb6ecb90d/713b7/IMG_20211006_232200.webp 680w,\n/static/ad8f512f9f55c159c75ce39cb6ecb90d/54376/IMG_20211006_232200.webp 1360w,\n/static/ad8f512f9f55c159c75ce39cb6ecb90d/0be89/IMG_20211006_232200.webp 2040w,\n/static/ad8f512f9f55c159c75ce39cb6ecb90d/71194/IMG_20211006_232200.webp 2720w,\n/static/ad8f512f9f55c159c75ce39cb6ecb90d/536fb/IMG_20211006_232200.webp 3028w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 1360px) 100vw, 1360px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/ad8f512f9f55c159c75ce39cb6ecb90d/2e524/IMG_20211006_232200.jpg 340w,\n/static/ad8f512f9f55c159c75ce39cb6ecb90d/d330d/IMG_20211006_232200.jpg 680w,\n/static/ad8f512f9f55c159c75ce39cb6ecb90d/6c26c/IMG_20211006_232200.jpg 1360w,\n/static/ad8f512f9f55c159c75ce39cb6ecb90d/afd2d/IMG_20211006_232200.jpg 2040w,\n/static/ad8f512f9f55c159c75ce39cb6ecb90d/f4749/IMG_20211006_232200.jpg 2720w,\n/static/ad8f512f9f55c159c75ce39cb6ecb90d/9041d/IMG_20211006_232200.jpg 3028w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 1360px) 100vw, 1360px\"\n          type=\"image/jpeg\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n          src=\"/static/ad8f512f9f55c159c75ce39cb6ecb90d/6c26c/IMG_20211006_232200.jpg\"\n          alt=\"IMG 20211006 232200\"\n          title=\"\"\n          src=\"/static/ad8f512f9f55c159c75ce39cb6ecb90d/6c26c/IMG_20211006_232200.jpg\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n      </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>For this pourpose I wrote a <a href=\"https://github.com/AlessioMorale/crsf_parser\">CRSF protocol parser</a> and a <a href=\"https://github.com/AlessioMorale/ros_crsf_driver\">ROS driver</a>.</p>\n<h3>Old DS4DRV bluetooth joypad</h3>\n<p>Teleop was previousluy handled using a bluetooth PS4 joypad as input device using <a href=\"https://pypi.org/project/ds4drv/\">DS4DRV</a></p>\n<h2>Video</h2>\n<p>Below a simple test after installing the four new motors and the unav2 prototype.</p>\n<p><div class=\"gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper\" style=\"padding-bottom: 50%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden; margin-bottom: 1.0725rem\" > <div class=\"embedVideo-container\"> <iframe title src=\"https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/1pnrorfGNso?rel=0\" class=\"embedVideo-iframe\" style=\"border:0; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; \" loading=\"lazy\" allowfullscreen sandbox=\"allow-same-origin allow-scripts allow-popups\"></iframe> </div> </div></p>\n<p>Find additional Slammer related blog entries <a href=\"/tag/slammer\">here</a></p>\n<h2>Additional pictures</h2>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/dc7a62251eb38d9f0a7ba24f91ceafb3/d1cca/IMG_20210423_173919.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin: 7vw 0; max-width: 1360px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 133.23529411764707%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/dc7a62251eb38d9f0a7ba24f91ceafb3/51a8e/IMG_20210423_173919.webp 340w,\n/static/dc7a62251eb38d9f0a7ba24f91ce